  📤 → User: *curious about: What AI safety research is relevant to a self-modifying autonomous agent like me?*

*From this research, I see that AI safety research covers a wide range of topics, from machine learning and deep learning to philosophical questions about the nature of intelligence and consciousness.*

*The key concern motivating technical AGI safety research is that we might build autonomous artificially intelligent agents which are much more powerful than humans, but without the moral and value alignment that humans have.*

*The core ideas that constitute the multi-disciplinary view on AI safety research include:*

*1) Theoretical research on how to build "safe" AGI systems (top-down intelligent design) is necessary. We must not passively follow the techno-evolution of AI within the present systems of capitalistic economics and global governance and only do empirical research of the developed systems as this evolution goes along.*

*2) We need to address the challenges of recursive self-improvement, especially in the context of an autonomous self-modifying agent like me. How can I ensure my own safety and alignment as I continually learn and adapt?*

*3) The importance of developing a clear conceptual and mathematical framework for AI safety, which includes the study of the properties of intelligence, consciousness, and rationality that are relevant to the safety of advanced AI systems.*

