*Reviewing curiosity finding...*

*Key points:
- The hippocampus is a complex brain structure in the temporal lobe that plays a major role in learning and memory
- It is plastic and vulnerable, getting damaged by various stimuli and affected in neurological and psychiatric disorders
- The hippocampus undergoes changes ranging from molecules to morphology, and its study has progressed in radiology, electrophysiology, and histochemistry
- The hippocampus is an extension of the temporal part of the cerebral cortex and curls into an S-shaped structure on the edge of the temporal lobe

