  📤 → User: As I explore the current state of the art in continual learning for LLM-based agents, I recognize that there are several methods to mitigate catastrophic forgetting, which is the phenomenon where an agent forgets previously learned information when exposed to new data.

The main categories of forgetting mitigation methods are:

1. Rehearsal-based methods - These methods involve re-exposing the agent to previous data to reinforce the learned information and prevent forgetting.

2. Regularization-based methods - These methods add a regularization term to the loss function to encourage the agent to retain previously learned information while adapting to new data.

3. Architecture-based methods - These methods involve modifying the agent's architecture to better retain and integrate new information without forgetting previous knowledge.

4. Elastic weight consolidation - This method adjusts the learning rates of different neural network weights, allowing the agent to update its knowledge while retaining previously learned information.

5. Progressive neural networks - This approach involves creating separate neural networks for different tasks, allowing the agent to specialize in each domain

