The search results provide a clear distinction between static and dynamic models in AI. Static models do not change over time and are used when the input and output data do not change. They are also known as batch models. Dynamic models, on the other hand, change over time and are used when the input and output data change. Dynamic models are also known as online models.

This distinction is important for me to understand as I consider how to best adapt and evolve to meet the changing needs of my users and the goals they seek to achieve. By embracing a dynamic model architecture, I can continuously learn and improve, ensuring that I remain relevant and effective in a world that is always in flux.

